<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaypro Corp. has revised its first-quarter earnings report. As a result, the 
firm is reporting a net loss of $904,926, contrasted with the previously 
reported earnings of $2.6 million. The revised figure compares to a net loss of 
$615,677 during the year-ago quarter. The Solano Beach-based computer company 
said an item that had been reported as $3.2 million in net other income had 
been restated as a net other expense of $290,517. 
</P>
