<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tenneco's fourth-quarter earnings rebounded from a loss a year ago, helped 
largely by an $867-million gain from the sale of its oil and gas businesses. 
The Houston-based diversified industrial company reported net income of $598 
million, contrasted with a loss of $176 million in the 1987 period. Revenue was 
$3.6 billion, up 13%. For all 1988, net income was $822 million, contrasted 
with a $218-million loss in 1987. Revenue totaled $13.2 billion, up 11%. 
</P>
