MIDEAST AIR SHOW DRAWS BIG TURNOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUBAI, United Arab Emirates 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two U.S. Navy F-18 Hornet aircraft displayed precision flying Thursday to mark 
the closing of one of the largest air shows ever in the Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
More than 200 exhibitors from around the world displayed aircraft and aviation 
technology during the five-day International Aerospace Exhibition in this 
Persian Gulf emirate. 
</P>
<P>
Combat aircraft were flown in by the United States, Britain, France and Italy. 
China presented a display of weapons that included tanks and artillery. 
</P>
<P>
