<P>
A 30-year-old Navy man apparently shot and wounded his 22-year-old wife during 
an argument early Thursday and then killed himself, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Curtis J. Johnson Jr. apparently shot his wife, Billette Rene Johnson, once in 
the chest as they argued just after midnight in the 5200 block of Orange Avenue 
in East San Diego. Johnson then walked out on the front lawn and shot himself 
once in the head with his .30-30 rifle. He was dead at the scene, police said. 
</P>
