<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
DRIVER KILLED IN CAR'S PLUNGE OFF FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aman was killed when he drove off the Foothill Freeway and plunged onto Van 
Nuys Boulevard in Lake View Terrace, the California Highway Patrol reported 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old La Canada man, whose name was not released pending notification 
of his family, was killed at 8:20 p.m. Wednesday when his eastbound car drifted 
to the right shoulder of the freeway, hit a guard rail and became airborne 
before landing on the boulevard below, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no other injuries. Officer Linda Powell said the CHP does not know 
why the car went off the freeway, and an autopsy is scheduled. 
</P>
