<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. District Court judge has dissolved a temporary restraining order that 
prevented Genetics Institute, a Cambridge, Mass.-based biotechnology firm, from 
manufacturing and selling an anti-anemia drug it is developing. The judge urged 
a speedy trial in the matter. Genetics Institute is involved in a series of 
patent infringement cases with Amgen, a Thousand Oaks-based biotechnology 
company that is developing its own version of erythropoietin. Amgen and 
Genetics Institute have applied to the Food and Drug Administration for 
approval to sell the drug here, and both, through partners, are trying to break 
into the European market. 
