<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ducommun Inc. expects to report a fourth-quarter loss and is negotiating with 
its bank, Security Pacific, to change an agreement that says Ducommun's 
fourth-quarter net loss cannot exceed $600,000. Ducommun, a Carson-based 
aerospace and electronics firm, said its fourth-quarter loss from operations 
would be less than the $1.6 million it lost in the third quarter but that it 
would be taking a $1.5-million writedown for excess inventory at its Jay-El 
unit and a $2-million charge for cost overruns at its AHF-Ducommun unit. 
</P>
