<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Museum of Art Assn. has received a $30,000 grant from 
the National Endowment for the Arts to support its "Evenings for Educators" 
program that provides visual arts resources and training for elementary and 
secondary teachers. In all, the National Endowment awarded $440,590 to 18 
projects that promote arts education in schools across the country. ALEENE 
MacMINN 
</P>
