<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: AMPLIFICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An item in Thursday's Morning Report prompted a number of cable television 
subscribers to call the Los Angeles City Department of Telecommunications 
asking about deposits they have made on channel changers and converter boxes. 
Cable companies are automatically required to return deposits with interest at 
the time service is disconnected, says Susan Herman, general manager of the 
department. She says that two Los Angeles area cable companies currently hold 
deposits: American Cable Systems, which serves Hollywood, Wilshire, Westchester 
and South-Central Los Angeles, and Cablevision, which took over Valley Cable 
and maintains deposits collected by that company. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
