<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEPPERDINE FACES SAN DIEGO IN WARMUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RAY RIPTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pepperdine, tied for first place in the West Coast Athletic Conference with 
Loyola Marymount and St. Mary's at 5-1, will play host to the University of San 
Diego at 7:30 tonight and to St. Mary's at 7:30 Saturday in Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego (6-12 overall, 1-5 in the WCAC) won its first conference game last 
Saturday, upsetting USF, 69-64, a night after the Dons handed St. Mary's its 
first conference loss, 62-55. 
</P>
<P>
The Toreros are led by 6-5 freshman guard Gylan Dottin of Santa Ana Saddleback 
High, who is averaging 13 points a game. RAY RIPTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020389-0108 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 13781 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 3, 1989, Friday, Home Edition 
