<P>
BLACK HISTORY PARADE TO STEP OFF SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 10th Annual Black History Parade is scheduled to start its nearly 2-mile 
trek through Santa Ana streets at 10 a.m. Saturday and culminate in a 4-hour 
"Unity Festival" at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Grand Marshals Ken Sagoes of the television show "What's Happening Now" and 
Larry Carroll of Channel 7 Eyewitness News will lead the 100-unit parade that 
will include floats and marching bands. The route is from the 15th Street down 
Main Street to Civic Center Drive. The parade, which Santa Ana officials said 
attracted about 25,000 spectators last year, will head west on Civic Center 
Drive to the festival at the stadium on Flower Street. Starting at 1 p.m., the 
celebration will feature continuous entertainment, food and craft booths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
