<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
TV'S TODD BRIDGES HELD IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Todd Bridges, best known for his role as Gary Coleman's brother on the 
television show "Diff'rent Strokes," was arrested for investigation of 
attempted murder after allegedly shooting another man five times, police said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges, 23, and Harvey Duckett, 30, were ordered held without bail at the 
Parker Center Jail. Police Sgt. Doug Tantee said they were arrested Thursday 
night in connection with the shooting and stabbing of Kenneth Clay, who was in 
critical but stable condition at Martin Luther King Jr.-Drew Medical Center. 
Clay told police he confronted the two men inside a vacant home that he was 
supposed to be watching on West 65th Street, a neighborhood plagued by rock 
cocaine dealers. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges has had several previous brushes with the law. In 1987 he received a 
suspended sentence after pleading no contest to charges of making a bomb threat 
and in 1983 he paid a $240 fine for carrying a concealed firearm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Todd Bridges Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
