<P>
BOMB EXPLODES NEAR HIROHITO FUNERAL SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bomb exploded today at a religious shrine less than a mile from where the 
late Emperor Hirohito's funeral will be held, and police said leftists opposed 
to Japan's imperial system were suspected of planting it. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the explosion at about 4 a.m. at the Togo Shrine in 
central Tokyo, said a spokesman for the Metropolitan Police Agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
