<TEXT>
<P>
Two young children, their mother and grandmother were fatally stabbed and their 
house set on fire early today, and police arrested the mother's boyfriend in 
the killings. 
</P>
<P>
Hammond Police Sgt. Ron Hill said Dennis Rourke, 25, of Gary was arrested on a 
preliminary homicide charge. The victims were identified by neighbors as 
Rourke's 19-year-old girlfriend, Mary Waggoner, their 4-month-old child, 
Waggoner's 2-year-old toddler and her 61-year-old mother, Betty Waggoner. 
</P>
