IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
EDMONTON STATUE TO HONOR GRETZKY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EDMONTON, Canada 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $75,000 life-sized, bronze statue of Wayne Gretzky will be erected at the 
Northlands Coliseum to honor the former Edmonton Oilers center's contribution 
to the city. 
</P>
<P>
A public rally that the hockey star will attend also is in the works, said 
Olivia Butti, chairwoman of a task force set up to decide on a tribute for 
Gretzky. 
</P>
<P>
The statue will be unveiled at the rally, probably in September. 
</P>
<P>
It will be a likeness of Gretzky with his arms raised, holding the Stanley Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
