<HEADLINE>
<P>
EVERT UPSET BY MCNEIL IN PAN PACIFIC TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Repeating her performance in the 1987 U.S. Open, American Lori McNeil upset 
Chris Evert today in the quarterfinals of the Pan Pacific Open tennis 
tournament in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
In the day's second upset, American Mary Joe Fernandez, ranked 14th in the 
world, romped over Gabriela Sabatini of Argentina, ranked No. 4, 6-2, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Martina Navratilova cruised into the semifinals, defeating West 
Germany's Claudia Kohde-Kilsch 6-2, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Playing before 3,200 spectators on artificial courts at Tokyo's Aoyamagakuin 
Memorial Hall, seventh-seeded McNeil outscored third-seeded Evert 6-2, 5-7, 
6-4. 
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals Saturday, McNeil meets American Zina Garrison, who downed 
compatriot Molly Van Nostrand 6-1, 6-0 in the quarterfinals. Navratilova plays 
Fernandez in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Top-Seeded Fendick Advances in Auckland 
</P>
<P>
In other women's tennis, top-seeded American Patty Fendick trounced Swede Maria 
Lindstrom 6-2, 6-0 today to advance to the semifinals of the Nutri-Metics 
International women's tennis tournament in Auckland, New Zealand. 
</P>
<P>
Fendick, from Sacramento, meets unseeded Donna Faber in the semifinals. Faber, 
17, from Bradenton, Fla., upset eighth-seeded American Beverly Bowes 3-6, 6-3, 
6-2. 
</P>
<P>
In other quarterfinal action, No. 6 Belinda Cordwell of New Zealand and No. 7 
Jo Durie of Britain also advanced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Lori McNeil shows backhand that helped upset Chris Evert. Associated 
Press 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
